\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 1. Introduction\b0\par
\par
\pard\b 1.1 Purpose of Phase 2\b0\par
\pard
The purpose of Phase 2 is to translate the Phase 1 problem definition into a concrete system design and a demonstrable Proof of Concept (PoC). For MediStock (Intelligent Medicine Inventory Management with Forecasting, Alerts, and IoT Integration), Phase 2 focuses on:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Translating the inventory and consumption-tracking problem into a complete web-system design (modules, workflows, data model).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Defining functional and non-functional requirements to ensure correctness, usability, and operational readiness.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Designing the architecture (MVC, services, database) and validating feasibility through an implemented PoC.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 1.2 Scope of Phase 2\b0\par
\pard
Phase 2 includes:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 System design and architecture (MVC, service-layer, database, UI views).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Detailed functional and non-functional requirements.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 High-level database design and data-flow design for core workflows.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 A working PoC demonstrating end-to-end modules: Drug, Stock, Consumption, Alerts, Reports, and AI/ML Predictions.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 2. System Overview\b0\par
\par
\pard\b 2.1 Product Perspective\b0\par
\pard
MediStock is a standalone web-based hospital inventory and consumption management system. It can be deployed in a hospital intranet environment and can be integrated in the future with procurement/supplier systems.\par
\par
High-level interactions:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Users interact via a web browser UI (Bootstrap/Twig pages).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The Symfony backend processes requests, applies business rules, and reads/writes to the MySQL database via Doctrine ORM.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Prediction services analyze consumption history and generate consumption forecasts and stockout timelines.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Deployment environment:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Web application (server-side rendered) running on PHP/Symfony.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 MySQL database (Docker container for development; production can use managed MySQL).\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 2.2 Major System Functions\b0\par
\pard
Key system functionalities include:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Drug catalog management (Create/Read/Update/Delete).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Stock management (increase, decrease, set stock; prevent negative stock).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Consumption logging (record usage; automatically deduct stock).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Low-stock alerts (threshold-based).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Reports (low-stock report and consumption usage report with filters).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 AI/ML predictions: consumption prediction and stockout prediction with confidence/urgency.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 2.3 User Classes and Characteristics\b0\par
\pard
Primary user roles (authentication is a future enhancement; PoC assumes trusted internal users):\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Pharmacy Staff: logs consumption, updates stock, responds to alerts.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Hospital Administrator / Inventory Manager: monitors stock, views reports, uses predictions for procurement planning.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 System Administrator (future): manages users/roles and configuration.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 3. Functional Requirements\b0\par
\par
\pard
The functional requirements (FR) are listed below.\par
\par
\pard\b Drug Management\b0\par
\pard
FR1: The system shall allow users to create a new drug with name, category, threshold, and initial stock quantity.\par
FR2: The system shall display a list of all drugs with current stock, threshold, and low-stock status.\par
FR3: The system shall allow users to view complete drug details.\par
FR4: The system shall allow users to edit drug details including threshold and stock quantity.\par
FR5: The system shall allow users to delete a drug with CSRF protection.\par
\par
\pard\b Stock Management\b0\par
\pard
FR6: The system shall provide a stock overview page listing all drugs and their stock levels.\par
FR7: The system shall allow users to increase stock by a given quantity.\par
FR8: The system shall allow users to decrease stock by a given quantity.\par
FR9: The system shall allow users to set the exact stock quantity.\par
FR10: The system shall prevent stock quantity from becoming negative.\par
\par
\pard\b Consumption Logging\b0\par
\pard
FR11: The system shall allow users to record drug consumption including drug, quantity, date/time, logged-by, and optional notes.\par
FR12: The system shall automatically deduct stock quantity when consumption is logged.\par
FR13: The system shall prevent logging consumption that would cause negative stock.\par
FR14: The system shall provide a consumption history page and allow viewing a single consumption record in detail.\par
\par
\pard\b Alerts and Reports\b0\par
\pard
FR15: The system shall detect low-stock drugs based on threshold and show them on an alerts page.\par
FR16: The system shall provide a low-stock report with shortage amounts.\par
FR17: The system shall provide a usage report with filtering by drug and date range.\par
FR18: The system shall provide summary metrics (totals/averages) for the usage report.\par
\par
\pard\b Dashboard\b0\par
\pard
FR19: The system shall provide a dashboard with total drugs, total stock items, and low-stock counts.\par
FR20: The system shall display recent consumption and top low-stock items on the dashboard.\par
FR21: The system shall provide quick-action navigation to common workflows (add drug, update stock, log consumption, view reports, predictions).\par
\par
\pard\b AI/ML Predictions\b0\par
\pard
FR22: The system shall generate consumption predictions for a selected drug for user-selected horizons (e.g., 7/14/30 days).\par
FR23: The system shall provide confidence levels (high/medium/low) for consumption predictions based on data consistency.\par
FR24: The system shall generate stockout predictions for all drugs and classify urgency (URGENT/WARNING/PREDICTED/SAFE).\par
FR25: The system shall provide a detailed prediction view for a selected drug including estimated stockout date and days remaining.\par
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 4. Non-Functional Requirements\b0\par
\par
\pard\b 4.1 Performance Requirements\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The system should load standard list pages (drugs/stock/consumption) within 2 seconds under normal local/intranet usage.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Reports and prediction generation should complete within 5 seconds for typical dataset sizes (hundreds to thousands of consumption rows).\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 4.2 Security Requirements\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The system shall protect state-changing forms using CSRF tokens.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The system shall prevent SQL injection using ORM parameterized queries.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The system shall mitigate XSS via template auto-escaping and input validation.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 (Future) The system shall implement authentication and role-based authorization for Admin/Staff roles.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 4.3 Usability Requirements\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The UI shall be responsive for desktop and mobile devices.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The system shall provide clear navigation (navbar + breadcrumbs) and visual status indicators (badges/colors) for stock state.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The system shall provide feedback for actions via flash messages (success/error).\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 4.4 Scalability and Maintainability\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The codebase shall follow modular MVC with separate controllers, forms, services, and templates.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Business logic (including ML prediction logic) shall be encapsulated in services to allow future extensions.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Database changes shall be managed via migrations to support controlled evolution.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 5. System Architecture and Design\b0\par
\par
\pard\b 5.1 System Architecture Diagram\b0\par
\pard
(High-level architecture diagram)\par
\par
\pard\li720
[Web Browser]\par
    |\par
    v\par
[Twig/Bootstrap UI Templates]\par
    |\par
    v\par
[Symfony Controllers]\par
    |\par
    v\par
[Service Layer: Stock Logic, Prediction Services]\par
    |\par
    v\par
[Doctrine ORM / Repositories]\par
    |\par
    v\par
[MySQL Database]\par
\pard\li0
\par
External libraries:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Chart.js for visualization on prediction pages.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 PHP-ML library (dependency) used for ML-related computations where applicable.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 5.2 Module-wise Design\b0\par
\pard
Module 1: Drug Management\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Responsibilities: CRUD for drugs, manage threshold and baseline information.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Inputs: drug details from forms.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Outputs: persisted Drug records; views for list/detail.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Module 2: Stock Management\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Responsibilities: adjust stock (increase/decrease/set) and enforce non-negative stock.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Inputs: stock adjustment action + quantity.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Outputs: updated Drug stockQuantity; user feedback messages.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Module 3: Consumption Logging\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Responsibilities: capture consumption events; deduct stock; maintain audit-like history.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Inputs: selected drug, quantity, consumedAt, loggedBy, notes.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Outputs: persisted Consumption record; updated stock.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Module 4: Alerts\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Responsibilities: compute low-stock list and summaries.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Inputs: Drug inventory state.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Outputs: low-stock view and recommended actions.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Module 5: Reports\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Responsibilities: generate low-stock and usage analytics with filters.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Inputs: optional drug filter and date-range filter.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Outputs: aggregated metrics and detailed tables.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Module 6: Predictions (AI/ML)\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Responsibilities: predict consumption and stockout dates; provide confidence and urgency classification.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Inputs: consumption history and current stock.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Outputs: prediction tables, charts, and actionable indicators.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 5.3 Data Flow Design\b0\par
\pard
Key data flows:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Add Drug: UI Form \u8594? Controller \u8594? Doctrine ORM \u8594? Database \u8594? Drug List/Detail.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Log Consumption: UI Form \u8594? Controller (validate) \u8594? Create Consumption \u8594? Update Drug stock \u8594? Database \u8594? Dashboard/Reports.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Alerts: Controller queries drugs \u8594? apply threshold logic \u8594? Alerts view.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Predictions: Controller fetches consumption history \u8594? Prediction Service \u8594? results to template \u8594? charts/tables.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b 5.4 Database Design (If Applicable)\b0\par
\pard
High-level ER relationship:\par
\pard\li720
Drug (1) \u8594? (Many) Consumption\par
\pard\li0
\par
Key entities and attributes:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Drug: id, name, category, threshold, stockQuantity, createdAt.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Consumption: id, drug (FK), quantity, consumedAt, loggedBy, notes.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 6. Technology Stack and Justification\b0\par
\par
\pard\b Frontend:\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Twig: server-side templating integrated with Symfony; fast development.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Bootstrap 5: responsive UI components and consistent styling.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Chart.js: simple, effective charts for predictions and analytics.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b Backend:\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Symfony 7.x (PHP 8.3): robust MVC framework, routing, DI, forms, validation.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Doctrine ORM: secure database access, migrations, entity mapping.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b Database:\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 MySQL 8: widely adopted relational DB; supports transactional integrity.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b Other Tools / Frameworks:\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Docker Compose: repeatable local DB environment for the PoC.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 PHP-ML: ML-related utilities and future extensibility for advanced models.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 7. Proof of Concept (PoC)\b0\par
\par
\pard\b 7.1 PoC Description\b0\par
\pard
The PoC for Phase 2 is a working web application that demonstrates:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 End-to-end drug inventory workflows (CRUD, stock updates).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Consumption logging with automatic stock deduction.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Low-stock alerts and reporting.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 AI/ML prediction pages for consumption forecasting and stockout predictions.\par
\pard\li0
\par
This validates feasibility by showing that the system can store real consumption history, enforce stock integrity rules, and generate actionable predictions based on historical data.\par
\par
\pard\b 7.2 PoC Demonstration Details\b0\par
\pard
Demonstrated features:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Dashboard: KPIs, top alerts, recent consumption, quick actions.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Drugs: create/list/view/edit/delete.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Stock: increase/decrease/set stock with safeguards.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Consumption: create logs and view history.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Alerts/Reports: low-stock list, low-stock report, usage report with filters.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Predictions: consumption prediction chart/table, stockout urgency classification.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Evidence to attach (to be provided by the group):\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Screenshots of main pages (Dashboard, Stock, Alerts, Reports, Predictions).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 (Optional) A short demo video or live demo link.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Current limitations:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Authentication/authorization is not implemented in the PoC (assumes trusted users).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Predictions are statistical/heuristic (moving average + trend) and can be improved with more advanced models.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 8. Testing and Validation Strategy\b0\par
\par
\pard
Testing and validation approach for the PoC:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Unit testing (recommended): services for prediction logic (moving average, trend, confidence scoring), and stock adjustment rules.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Integration testing: controller workflows for consumption logging and automatic stock deduction.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Manual testing: end-to-end scenario testing across all modules; form validation checks; negative stock prevention; report filter validation.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 9. Risks, Challenges, and Mitigation\b0\par
\par
\pard\b Identified Risks\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Technical complexity: ensuring consistent stock integrity while logging consumption and editing inventory.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Data quality: predictions depend on sufficient and consistent consumption history.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Usability: risk of user errors in stock updates and consumption logging.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Deployment constraints: dependency on Docker/MySQL setup for PoC environments.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\b Mitigation Strategies\b0\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Enforce validation rules (no negative stock) and clear UI feedback (flash messages).\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Provide confidence levels and bounds to communicate prediction uncertainty.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Use Bootstrap UI patterns and clear forms to reduce input mistakes.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Document setup steps and provide troubleshooting guide for database startup.\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
\par
\pard\b 10. Phase 2 Outcomes and Readiness for Phase 3\b0\par
\par
\pard
Phase 2 outcomes:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Completed system design aligned with modular MVC architecture.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Implemented a working PoC covering all major modules and user workflows.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Implemented AI/ML prediction services and UI visualization for decision support.\par
\pard\li0
\par
Readiness for Phase 3:\par
\pard\li720
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 The system is ready for refinement and production-hardening: authentication, role-based access, audit logs, and improved ML models.\par
\pard\li720\bullet \tx720 Phase 3 can focus on deployment planning, security hardening, advanced analytics, and integrations (supplier/procurement).\par
\pard\li0
\par
\pard\qc ________________________________________\par
